00:11:53.710 --> 00:11:58.560
and for our readers was
why is this happening now?

00:11:58.560 --> 00:12:00.310
Is it unusual?

00:12:00.310 --> 00:12:04.930 position:56%
And what turns out to be the case,
when you look back at the long sweep

00:12:04.930 --> 00:12:09.740
of history is that the
strains we're facing now,

00:12:09.740 --> 00:12:13.470
the fights we're having now, the
fact that the right to vote seems

00:12:13.470 --> 00:12:16.040
to require a fight to vote.

00:12:16.040 --> 00:12:17.830
That is consequential.

00:12:17.830 --> 00:12:20.190
These debates are fierce.

00:12:20.190 --> 00:12:24.930
They are challenging,
but they are not new.

00:12:24.930 --> 00:12:29.920
In fact, this question of the fight
to vote has been at the center

00:12:29.920 --> 00:12:32.370
of American history,
from the very beginning.

00:12:32.370 --> 00:12:34.970
It's been at the heart
of political debates.

00:12:34.970 --> 00:12:39.540
It's often been a fulcrum
