00:14:46.080 --> 00:14:48.710
That was the tradition
in effect handed

00:14:48.710 --> 00:14:51.040
down from England in the continent.

00:14:51.040 --> 00:14:54.280
But even then it was controversial.

00:14:54.280 --> 00:14:58.740
The power of those revolutionary
ideals began to crack the certainty

00:14:58.740 --> 00:15:06.760
that surrounded that approach
in 1776 in Pennsylvania,

00:15:06.760 --> 00:15:13.030
Benjamin Franklin led a
working man's revolt in one

00:15:13.030 --> 00:15:16.420
of the only places in
the whole revolution

00:15:16.420 --> 00:15:19.100
where it really looked like,
you know the French Revolution.

00:15:19.100 --> 00:15:23.050
Where a giant throng of people
stormed the State House.

00:15:23.050 --> 00:15:27.220
He led a working man's revolt,
demanding a new government,

00:15:27.220 --> 00:15:29.350
and demanding as its key element

00:15:29.350 --> 00:15:31.790
that the property requirement
for voting be ended.

00:15:31.790 --> 00:15:34.260
He actually was the
president of the convention

00:15:34.260 --> 00:15:36.130
that wrote the Constitution
of Pennsylvania.

00:15:36.130 --> 00:15:39.310
It was the world's most radical
